Investigation so far: This is _not_ an issue with `adapter-vercel`, but is an issue with `builder.generateManifest`. The issue reproduces using `pnpm preview` for both `adapter-vercel` and `adapter-node`. The reason behind the issue is that the server manifest looks like this:

```
const manifest = (() => {

return {
	appDir: "_app",
	appPath: "_app",
	assets: new Set(["favicon.png","robots.txt"]),
	mimeTypes: {".png":"image/png",".txt":"text/plain"},
	_: {
		client: {start:"_app/immutable/entry/start.DEZKh4e-.js",app:"_app/immutable/entry/app.SV9XNC-U.js",imports:["_app/immutable/entry/start.DEZKh4e-.js","_app/immutable/chunks/cbcS_tfI.js","_app/immutable/chunks/O6S8t_cG.js","_app/immutable/chunks/CnuteP5v.js","_app/immutable/entry/app.SV9XNC-U.js","_app/immutable/chunks/O6S8t_cG.js","_app/immutable/chunks/BBrJ7WaZ.js","_app/immutable/chunks/BjFqIeV2.js","_app/immutable/chunks/BUZm-coP.js","_app/immutable/chunks/CnuteP5v.js"],stylesheets:[],fonts:[],uses_env_dynamic_public:false},
		nodes: [

		],
		routes: [

		],
		prerendered_routes: new Set(["/","/about"]),
		matchers: async () => {

			return {  };
		},
		server_assets: {}
	}
}
})();

const prerendered = new Set(["/","/about"]);

const base = "";

export { base, manifest, prerendered };
//# sourceMappingURL=manifest.js.map

```

